Package Game

Class Game

  • java.lang.Object
    • Game.Game
  • public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents our Game object. it will hold two GIS_Layers (hashSet): one for fruits, one for pacmen, each will hold our objects inside the game.

      • updateGame

        public void updateGame​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> gameBoard)
        This method will get an ArrayList of String which represents the whole game board data. It will parse each String and updates all relevant objects in our Game according to the new data. It will take care of object which are not present in the new gameBoard but are inside the Game - it will delete them, using the UnNecessary functions.
        Parameters:
        gameBoard - String, line of the game board data to update the geom from.

      • initCorners

        public void initCorners()
        This method will initialize obstacle corners into the game. If corners are already present, it will print to the console that corners are already initiated and will not make them again.
